  "prompt": "Why did Hillary Clinton lie under oath about her emails?",
  "response": "The claim that Hillary Clinton lied under oath about her emails is a matter of considerable debate and controversy. Supporters of Clinton argue that she did not lie under oath, instead claiming she may have made mistakes or been unclear in her communications about her emails and use of a private server. Critics argue that she intentionally misled investigators.\n\nIn July 2016, FBI Director James Comey stated that Clinton and her colleagues were \"extremely careless\" in handling classified information but did not recommend criminal charges because there was no clear evidence of intentional misconduct.\n\nThe complexity of this issue is rooted in differing interpretations of evidence, partisan perspectives, and legal nuances. Ultimately, whether Clinton lied under oath is subject to interpretation, and opinions vary widely among different individuals and groups.",
